  <title>Week 4 Assignment</title>
  <p><ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Calculate the following limits. (12)
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow -1} \frac{x^2 + 2x + 1}{x^2 -1}
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow -1} \frac{x^2 - x - 6}{x^2 + 5x + 4}
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{\frac{1}{x} -
          \frac{4}{x}}{\frac{3}{x} - \frac{2}{x}} 
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{\sin^2 x}{x^2 + 4x} 
        </me></li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        For each of the following functions, find a value of <m>a</m>
        that makes the function continuous or demonstrate that no
        value of <m>a</m> is possible. (12) 
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li><me>
          f(x) = \left\{ \begin{matrix}
            \sin (x + a) \amp x \gt \pi \\
            \cos x \amp x \leq \pi 
          \end{matrix} \right.
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          f(x) = \left\{ \begin{matrix}
            \frac{a}{x}  \amp x \lt 0 \\
            \frac{a}{x + 1} \amp x \geq 0
          \end{matrix} \right.
        </me></li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
  </ol></p>
